      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy decision table into table J09B_temp where the tour starts with J09B.\\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\\n3. Classify meter reading type. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n    - Use sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n    - Use net data customer table entries.\\n8. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09B using column names: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n9. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address: meter.readings@evu.com, file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\\n10. Delete temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_3295bed5-e859-42da-b452-3b1f8aaaf473"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "6bc8b78a-db1b-46d6-9a0a-a2890a1a68e1",
        "tool_call_id": "call_xlttpx44",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy decision table into table J09B_temp where the tour starts with J09B.\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\n3. Classify meter reading type. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\".\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER using EQUNR.\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n    - Use sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n    - Use net data customer table entries.\n8. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09B using column names: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n9. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address: meter.readings@evu.com, file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\n10. Delete temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
